<paragraph blockId="104.[189,1399,595,694]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Troschel" authorityYear="1842" box="[315,468,595,621]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiacantha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[315,468,595,621]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Ophiacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with moderately large LAPs; outer surface stereom rather finely meshed, devoid of vertical striation; no spur on outer proximal and inner distal edges; up to seven spine articulations on strongly elevated distal portion of LAP; row of spine articulations strongly protruding dorsalwards.
</paragraph>
